pr_title: Allow usergroups in typeahead with or without @ prefix.
pr_body:
Earlier typeahead did not include user groups when user typed `@` in the pil input, thus there were complains about having
confusing flow for adding user groups to streams. So we allow user groups in pill typeahead as this helps in having a less confusing flow in adding user groups to streams.

Fixes: #22448.

pr_title: static: Move svg for check box in stream_settings_ui to static folder.
pr_body:
<!-- Describe your pull request here.-->

Fixes: Moves svg for check mark in `stream_settings_ui` to static folder. This is to avoid exclude rules for style rules in handlebars templates.
Related thread: https://chat.zulip.org/#narrow/stream/49-development-help/topic/Style.20attribute.20in.20handlebars

Currently I am not sure about the naming, I have used for icon file so feedback on that would be helpful. One other thing I am not sure about is the size difference between putting inline svg and putting it as zulip-icon. `.zulip-icon` class sets font weight as `normal !important` so the size of check mark when used as zulip-icon (after putting in `static/shared/icons` directory) is little smaller. Attaching ss for reference:
- Using as inline svg:
   
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/63504956/178113746-f476e100-e675-4a33-8a27-930af5cbbf70.png)

- Using as zulip-icon (after putting in `static/shared/icons` directory) :
   
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/63504956/178113806-2cfb1e89-446b-4dd3-9cda-81062155678f.png)

pr_body:

Its behaviour should be similar to `q` for stream filter toggler.
A follow-up for #18724.

pr_title: Deduplicate templates for stream privacy icon.
pr_body:
We had three templates that were related to setting icon based
on stream type. We kill these dupilcate templates to have a
common template `stream_privacy_icon.hbs` for this. 

Further plan on this is to have a separate directory for such
commonly used widgets. I'll make changes for that soon after this
PR.

https://chat.zulip.org/#narrow/stream/6-frontend/topic/duplicate.20stream.20icon.20templates
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 677886649, 'comment_body': 'Do we need to wrap a div around these elements, rather than having the color and CSS class be parameters to the template? It feels a little awkward.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 28, 0, 24, 18, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 681089362, 'comment_body': 'This is for 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/63504956/127887256-6e03ab61-9f50-4575-92af-a661f3343128.png)

So in this particular case wrapping div is the colored box surrounding that icon. So it has its own positioning logic and just different icons in it.

And most of the widget that use this icon templates have generally a span/div that handles all positioning/style logics and just has difference of icon inside it. Would it be better to keep style logic (which generally depends on places where it is used) to be separate from this?
